&lt;p&gt;Research Radiographer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced therapeutic radiographer with a keen interest in research and clinical trials for the opportunity to work with the Cancer Clinical Trials Team at Weston Park Cancer Centre, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. The post holder will have responsibility for a portfolio of locally recruiting multi-centre cancer clinical trials including those involving radiotherapy. This involves the delivery of direct and indirect care for trial participants, including the informed consent process, and the collection of accurate data. An important aspect of the role will be to liaise with the radiotherapy team to ensure new trials are set up in a timely manner and radiotherapy treatments are planned and given as per trial protocol. This post could provide an opportunity for a therapeutic radiographer to develop clinical research skills. We are looking for someone who is keen to learn and has excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Radiotherapy Department is situated in a purpose built oncology hospital and is one of four hospitals comprising Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. There is easy access to the beautiful countryside of Derbyshire and shopping in Sheffield city centre and nearby Meadowhall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The aim of this post is to provide sound, accurate clinical research data on patients who have been entered into local, national and international oncology clinical trials and be responsible for all trial documentation according to Good Clinical Practice guidelines/EU directive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This modern department comprises of seven Varian linear accelerators, including four Truebeam (two of which are Truebeam STX). Intensity Modulated Radiotherapy, Image Guided Radiotherapy and Volumetric Modulated Arc Therapy are standard practice across the department. There is an orthovoltage &amp; superficial unit and two new Philips CT scanners with virtual simulation and Varian RGSC gating system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer radiotherapy for paediatric patients and deliver SABR, CHART, DIBH and TBI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital adjoins the Sheffield University Clinical Trials Centre and there is a dedicated team of research and development radiographers who co-ordinate an active clinical trials portfolio and are developing an active local research programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital adjoins the Cancer Clinical Trials Centre and there are dedicated research radiographers who co-ordinate an active clinical trials portfolio and are developing an active local research programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a clinical placement site for student radiographers from Sheffield Hallam University and all staff are actively involved in the education and assessment of student radiographers.&lt;/p&gt;
